# MCP Server Setup Guide

## What is an MCP Server?

**MCP (Model Context Protocol)** servers extend Bob's capabilities by connecting it to external
tools, data sources, and services — such as web fetching, databases, APIs, and more.

---

## Prerequisites

Before setting up an MCP server, ensure the required runtime is installed on your machine:

| Runtime | Used For | Check Command | Install URL |
|---|---|---|---|
| Node.js (`npx`) | Most MCP servers | `node --version` | https://nodejs.org |
| Python (`uvx`) | Python-based servers | `uvx --version` | https://docs.astral.sh/uv/getting-started/installation/ |
| Docker | Container-based servers | `docker --version` | https://docs.docker.com/get-started/get-docker/ |

---

## Config File Locations

MCP servers are configured in a JSON file. There are two scopes:

| Scope | File Path | When to Use |
|---|---|---|
| **Global** | `~/.bob/settings/mcp.json` | Available in ALL workspaces |
| **Workspace** | `.bob/mcp.json` (in project root) | Only for THIS project |

> ⚠️ If both files define a server with the same name, the **workspace** config takes priority.

---

## Config File Structure

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "<server-name>": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "<mcp-package-name>"],
      "env": {
        "API_KEY": "your-api-key"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### Config Fields Reference

| Field | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `command` | Yes (local) | Executable to run: `npx`, `uvx`, `node`, or absolute path |
| `args` | Yes (local) | Array of arguments passed to the command |
| `url` | Yes (remote) | URL for remote MCP servers (mutually exclusive with `command`) |
| `headers` | No | HTTP headers for remote servers (e.g. auth tokens) |
| `env` | No | Environment variables injected into the server process |
| `disabled` | No | Set `true` to disable without deleting the entry |
| `disabledTools` | No | Array of tool names to suppress from this server |
| `alwaysAllow` | No | Array of tool names to auto-approve (skip confirmation prompt) |
| `timeout` | No | Connection timeout in ms (e.g. `30000` for 30 seconds) |
| `groups` | No | Restrict server tools to specific Bob modes (e.g. `["plan", "agent"]`) |

> ⚠️ **Local** servers use `command` + `args`. **Remote** servers use `url`. Never set both.

