## Example: Fetch MCP Server (Used in This Project)

This is the server configured for live web access (e.g. Consul documentation):

**File:** `~/.bob/settings/mcp.json`

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "fetch": {
      "command": "mcp-fetch-server",
      "args": [],
      "disabled": false
    }
  }
}
```

**Package:** `mcp-fetch-server` (install once globally: `npm install -g mcp-fetch-server`)

**What it does:** Allows Bob to fetch any public URL in real-time, enabling live access to
documentation, APIs, and websites. Supports HTML, Markdown, plain text, JSON, and YouTube
transcripts.

> ⚠️ **Do not use `mcp-fetch`** (a different npm package). It requires Puppeteer/Chromium and
> its install frequently fails, leaving a broken binary. Use `mcp-fetch-server` instead.

---

## Multiple Servers in One File

You can define multiple servers in the same config file:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "fetch": {
      "command": "mcp-fetch-server",
      "args": []
    },
    "github": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@modelcontextprotocol/server-github"],
      "env": {
        "GITHUB_TOKEN": "your-token"
      }
    },
    "postgres": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@modelcontextprotocol/server-postgres"],
      "env": {
        "POSTGRES_CONNECTION_STRING": "postgresql://user:pass@localhost/db"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

