## Useful MCP Servers

| Server Package | Install Command | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `mcp-fetch-server` ✅ | `npm install -g mcp-fetch-server` | Fetch URLs (HTML, MD, text, JSON, YouTube) |
| `@modelcontextprotocol/server-github` | `npm install -g @modelcontextprotocol/server-github` | GitHub repos, issues, PRs |
| `@modelcontextprotocol/server-postgres` | `npm install -g @modelcontextprotocol/server-postgres` | Query PostgreSQL databases |
| `@modelcontextprotocol/server-sqlite` | `npm install -g @modelcontextprotocol/server-sqlite` | Query SQLite databases |
| `@modelcontextprotocol/server-filesystem` | `npm install -g @modelcontextprotocol/server-filesystem` | Access files outside workspace |
| `@modelcontextprotocol/server-slack` | `npm install -g @modelcontextprotocol/server-slack` | Slack messages and channels |
| `@modelcontextprotocol/server-brave-search` | `npm install -g @modelcontextprotocol/server-brave-search` | Web search via Brave Search API |

> 💡 **Tip:** Pre-installing packages globally with `npm install -g` avoids the startup delay
> that `npx -y` causes each time Bob connects (npx re-downloads if not cached).
